The FireRed project established the original public reference for connecting an
LLM agent to a Pokemon emulator through an emulator script, bridge service,
agent/action loop, memory/state surface, and dashboard.

This public HeartGold release does not vendor the FireRed source tree, mGBA
bridge, FireRed ROM data, `pokefirered` submodule, or FireRed symbol file.

The HeartGold harness is its own Nintendo DS/BizHawk implementation, including
HeartGold-specific Lua and Python bridge code, decoded RAM observation,
map/navigation/interactable surfaces, action verification, Codex Desktop
endpoints, dashboard artifacts, and benchmark-oriented tooling.

No Pokemon ROMs, BIOS files, savestates, game assets, API keys, or live run
artifacts are included in this repository.
